text.section:
No later than ninety (90) days following July 15, 2002, the department shall promulgate administrative regulations requiring all insurers to report information on a calendar quarter basis on prompt payment of claims to providers, as defined in KRS 304.17A-700, that shall be limited to the following:
The number of clean claims received by the insurer, its agent, or designee during the reporting period;
The percentage of clean claims received by the insurer, its agent, or designee that were:
Adjudicated within the claims payment timeframe;
Adjudicated within one (1) to thirty (30) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
Adjudicated within thirty-one (31) to sixty (60) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
Adjudicated within sixty-one (61) to ninety (90) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
Adjudicated more than ninety (90) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe; and
Not yet adjudicated;
The percentage of clean claims received during the reporting quarter that were paid and not denied or contested:
Within the claims payment timeframe;
Within one (1) to thirty (30) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
Within thirty-one (31) to sixty (60) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
Within sixty (60) to ninety (90) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe;
More than ninety (90) days from the end of the claims payment timeframe; and
Not yet paid;
Amount of interest paid; and
For clean claims received during the reporting quarter that were not denied or contested, the percentage of the total dollar amount of those claims that were paid within the claims payment timeframe.
